rComments: His class was kinda easy. He's very reasonable and competent.

Pace of the course was a bit off: we moved really slowly before the term test and suddenly started sprinting through the rest of the material afterwards. Doesn't really give you any intuition about the topics, but he does walk through the textbook proofs in an understandable way. Follows almost every definition with hundreds of examples.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Hilarious']

rComments: He's a super nice Prof. Especially for first year students. The problem sets were pretty much challenging and took me a whole week to figure but I think that's because I never went to office hours. However the final was much easier than the assignments
Great prof. Super organised, knowledgeable and pleasant.
Good prof, problem sets can get hard but nice and easy final
Pretty decent prof. His notes are very well done and detailed and the course is very structured. Very organised prof.

It's math, so overall grade is mainly midterm (30%) and final (50%), with 20% homework (weekly problem set). The problem sets actually help you learn the stuff. Prof is really nice, very accessible after class and during office hours. He explains things to you and answers questions very patiently. As long as you want to learn, he is there to help!

This class was my hardest of so far taken, but it did worth it. The prof is amazing, TAs were a little off, but that's imho. Take it, if you're ready to work and receive hard HW feedback. Tests were way easier than everything we did in HWs and lectures, so that's a plus. Tutorials were lame and clearly unnecessary.

MAT 240 was difficult but Prof Meinrenken made the class bearable. He is quite accessible, my study group emailed him at about 11 am one day and he set up a meeting with us at 3 pm the same day. He is very friendly and a good prof. I highly recommend at least trying the course if you are interested.
Very nice

Great teacher! The enthusiasm he brings to his lectures are contagious. Seriously, Mien takes what could be a boring class and makes it interesting. Also a very understanding, all around nice guy. If you have a chance to take his class do it!
He is the nicest!!

Clear, helpful, great notes, and great explanations. Noticed that he actually looks around the class for cues that he should elaborate on something, which is priceless in a prof. Gave helpful hints during test review. Overall, a great professor!

Meinrenken's the best. His lectures really help you understand what calculus actually means. Instead of just a bunch of notation, he tells you how to interpret what you see. He has a Ph.D. in Physics and teaches like it. Being a Physics student, found it very useful. Emphasis is on understanding instead of blind application of format and notation.
Incredibly knowledgeable, stuttering becomes less of an issue by the end of the year, also enjoy his "i can't help you if you're stupid" shrug. Always well-prepared, very nerdy jokes.

Always comes to class super-prepared. Notes are clear, concise and his proofs are often better than those in the textbook. Does midterm review that is very helpful, and always answers questions during and after class. Clearly loves math and it shows in the quality of his lectures.
Effective and consistent.

One of the greatest professors, trully. Extremely well prepared and organized - the lectures just flow. Some proofs are hard to understand, but the clarity and detail writing of his makes it all understandable after you read the proof later on.

Oh the nervous german, that crazy stuttering of his and the looking away when you would ask him questions.  He was still an awesomely funny guy though, provided many laughs with his signature 'I can't help you if you are too stupid' shrug.  Fun course, tough, but fun.
well organized lecture, helpful problem sets.
(Diff Geometry I and II) Extremely neat.  Extremely well prepared.  Didn't think the problem sets/tests helped too much, though.
extremely well organized, clear lectures, neat board-writing.
Very clear and organized in his presentation.
he has the pronounciation problem and also he stutters
